Add `cursor_style` and `cursor_blink` options to opencode TUI config.

Upstream `tui-schema.ts` ships only color/scroll/diff settings — cursor
appearance (block vs line, blink on/off) isn't exposed.  This patch:

  1. Adds a `CursorStyle` Schema literal (`"block" | "line" | "underline"`)
     and registers `cursor_style` + `cursor_blink` on the `TuiInfo` schema,
     so values written to `~/.config/opencode/tui.json` survive validation.
  2. Threads a per-component `cursorStyle` memo (read from `tuiConfig`)
     into every `TextareaRenderable` JSX site, so all text inputs honor
     the configured style/blink.

Upstream already imports `useTuiConfig` in these files (and declares
`tuiConfig` locally where applicable), so this patch only adds the new
schema fields, the per-component memos, and the `cursorStyle={cursorStyle()}`
prop on each textarea.  Files touched:

  - packages/opencode/src/cli/cmd/tui/config/tui-schema.ts
  - packages/opencode/src/cli/cmd/tui/component/prompt/index.tsx
  - packages/opencode/src/cli/cmd/tui/routes/session/permission.tsx
  - packages/opencode/src/cli/cmd/tui/routes/session/question.tsx
  - packages/opencode/src/cli/cmd/tui/ui/dialog-export-options.tsx
  - packages/opencode/src/cli/cmd/tui/ui/dialog-prompt.tsx

